|Means "strong, nice" in Mongolian.
|-
|Bataar
|Means "hero, knight" in Mongolian.
|-
|Batbayar
|Means "strong joy" in Mongolian.
|-
|Batu
|Means "strong, firm" in Mongolian.
|-
|Batuhan
|Combination of Batu and Turkish ''han'' meaning "khan, ruler, leader", referring to the 13th-century Mongol ruler Batu Khan.
|-
|Batukhan
|Means "firm ruler" in Mongolian.
|-
|Batzorig
|Means "courageous, strong" in Mongolian.
